y_out  (OR producing carry)\n\nLast carry -> final z bit.\n\n#### Detection strategy:\nAnalyze gate structure to find violations of the adder pattern. For each bit position, check that:\n1. There's an XOR of xNN and yNN\n2. There's an XOR that produces zNN (for bits >= 1, it XORs partial sum with carry)\n3. The AND/OR gates follow the pattern\n4. Any gate whose output doesn't match expected role has been swapped\n\nKey rules for identifying swaps:\n- XOR gates should either take x/y inputs OR produce z outputs (not AND/OR intermediate wires)\n- AND gates should never produce z outputs (except maybe the final carry)\n- OR gates should never produce z outputs (except maybe the final carry) \n- OR gates produce carries, AND gates produce generate/propagate signals\n\nWrite thorough tests covering:\n1. simulate: basic gates, chained gates, all gate types\n2. findSwappedWires: construct a correct adder, swap 4 pairs of outputs, verify detection\n\nRun tests. Fix failures. Don't stop until tests pass.\" -y 2>&1","description":"Dispatch to Gemini for implementation","timeout":180000},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":165,"cache_read_input_tokens":19505,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":165},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7fe66ef0-d5d2-4812-aac6-1e203713ae0a","uuid":"c316aa0b-20b1-425c-8ea0-a0bdfd1329fc"}
